*Radishes were easily available in the markets of [[Westgate]], an rowdy city on the [[Dragon Reach]].
*Hardy root vegetables were very common in the areas of the [[Land of the Lions]], away from rivers. Radishes, [[onion]], and [[carrot]]s were grown by people of lesser means.
*The abbey of the [[Goldenfields]] on the [[Sword Coast North]] grew carrots, onions, [[squash]], [[tomatoe]]s, [[potato]]es, radishes, and other vegetables.
*The town of [[Shadowdale]] in the [[Dalelands]] cultivated radishes.
*In [[Cormyr]], various produce, including radishes passed through [[Ghars]] on its way from farming communities to tables across the country.
*The farming village of [[Elmwood]] grew radishes.{{Cite polyhedron/77/The Everwinking Eye: Moonsea Shores|7}}
*The [[hin]] farming village of [[Anqa Vled]] on the [[River Chionthar]] cultivated radishes, as well as [[parsnip]]s, carrots, [[marrow]]s, [[asparagus]]. All of these were used in baking the town's specialty [[spiced vegetable bread]].{{Cite dragon/269/The New Adventures of Volo: Hin Nobody Knows|86}}
*The towns of [[Bargewright Inn]], [[Grunwald]] and [[Hardbuckler]] grew and offered radishes in their inns and tavern.
*In [[the Vast]], radishes were grown in the hamlet of [[Sevenecho (hamlet)|Sevenecho]].<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/87/The Everwinking Eye: Sevenecho, Then and Now|8}}
